A.2 — nc_webdav_write_file silent truncation at ~20KB
======================================================
Writes via nc_webdav_write_file return status 201 but the on-server file
is corrupted — content truncated near 20KB. Documented in Gary's
auto-memory; corroborated repeatedly during 2026-04 work. The NC MCP
plan was split into two files because the limit blocks single-file
delivery — recursive confirmation of the bug.

Root cause (verified 2026-04-27): the truncation is upstream of the
MCP server itself — the MCP framework's JSON-RPC transport silently
truncates string parameter values above an internal buffer size. Server-
side webdav.write_file did a single httpx PUT with no chunking, so the
already-truncated body was PUT to NC verbatim.

Fix shape
=========
write_file now splits on size:
- ≤ CHUNK_THRESHOLD (1 MB):  single PUT (existing behaviour)
- > CHUNK_THRESHOLD:         NC v2 chunked upload
  (MKCOL /remote.php/dav/uploads/<user>/<chunk-id>/  →
   PUT each CHUNK_SIZE-byte chunk as 00000001, 00000002, ...  →
   MOVE .file with Destination header to assemble)

Returns now include bytes_written (and chunks/chunk_id for chunked
writes) so callers can detect-and-error on size mismatch rather than
silently relying on a 201 response.

Threshold rationale
===================
1 MB is well above the 20 KB observed cap (so all 'normal' callers
exit through chunked upload reliably) and well below the typical PHP
upload_max_filesize default of 8M-128M (so Nextcloud accepts the
chunked finalisation MOVE without server-side rejection).

What this fix does NOT address
==============================
The MCP framework's silent client-side truncation is upstream of this
MCP server. Workarounds for callers with very large bodies:
- Chunk client-side before invoking nc_webdav_write_file
- Use base64 content-type to transit binary safely (subject to the same
  cap, but failure is more visible)
A future MCP-framework fix would reject oversized JSON-RPC string
params at the transport layer rather than truncating silently.

Verification
============
tests/client/webdav/test_size_limit.py — sanity tests on threshold and
chunk-size constants. Live size-roundtrip tests deferred to the
integration suite (REQUIRES_LIVE_NC=1).

Refs
====
- Plan: Documents/Projects/NC/NC-MCP-Plan.md § A.2
- Per-regression analysis: Documents/Projects/NC/regressions/A2-webdav-truncation.md
